<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907640>
    dc:description "FIGURE 53. Portanus adenomari sp. nov. Female “internal” sternite VIII, dorsal view (connected to the sternite VII), showing the small sclerotized areas (black arrows) that are located between the valvifers I (not shown). Scale bar = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3907640/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907630>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–10. Portanus adenomari sp. nov. Male holotype (1, 8): 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted); 8, lateral habitus. Male paratype (2–7, 9, 10): 2, right forewing, dorsal view; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, aedeagus, ventral view; 7, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, head and anterior thorax, anterior view; 10, head and anterior thorax, ventral view. Scale bars: 1, 2, 8–10 = 1 mm; 3–7 = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3907630/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907632>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–21. Portanus adenomari sp. nov. Female paratype: 11, sternite VII, ventral view; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valvula I, lateral view; 14, apical portion of valvula I; 15, valvula II, lateral view; 16, apical portion of valvula II; 17, gonoplac, lateral view; 18, dorsal habitus; 19, ventral habitus; 20, lateral habitus; 21 head and anterior thorax, anterior view. Scale bars: 11–17 = 0.2 mm; 18–21 = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3907632/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

